50|$|In cryptography, a web {{of trust}} is a concept used in PGP, GnuPG, and other OpenPGP-compatible systems to {{establish}} {{the authenticity of the}} binding between a public key and its owner. Its decentralized <b>trust</b> <b>model</b> is an alternative to the centralized <b>trust</b> <b>model</b> of a public key infrastructure (PKI), which relies exclusively on a certificate authority (or a hierarchy of such). As with computer networks, there are many independent webs of trust, and any user (through their identity certificate) can be a part of, and a link between, multiple webs.|$|E
