50|$|In Scotland, the Enterprise <b>Trust</b> <b>model</b> was {{originally}} {{established in the}} early 1980s in an environment when the Scottish economy was undergoing significant change. Traditional industries such as coal mining, steel, shipbuilding and heavy engineering were all in decline. This period of economic transition impacted significantly on communities across Scotland and in response, enterprise trusts were established as locally led initiatives to support the regeneration of these communities through focusing on small businesses.|$|E
